description: An astonishing afternoon: Dan Morgenstern told stories -- true and first-hand -- to my video camera and to you.  If you don't know Mister Morgenstern, you need to brush up on your Jazzspeare. The subject here at first is Jimmy Rowles, then Dan comments on the way jazz brought black and white together in a then-segregated nation, remembers military service in Georgia, and tells us what the best potato salad in Harlem was.  Stick with it.  Recorded on March 3, 2017, at Dan's home, by Michael Steinman for JAZZ LIVES (http://www.jazzlives.wordpress.com)
